  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Strengthening producer leadership of Cafedirect producers</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Cafedirect Producers&#x2019; Foundation (CPF) is a UK-registered charity that works with smallholder tea, coffee and cocoa farmer organisations in Africa, Latin America and Asia. CPF focuses on strengthening smallholder farmers&#x2019; access to the training, education and information services they need to improve their farming practices and livelihoods.
CPF is the result of an evolutionary process that started with producer support through Cafedirect plc&#x2019;s Producer Partnership Programme (PPP). To give a greater voice to producer partners, Cafedirect offered producer partners the opportunity to purchase shares in Cafedirect plc and established Cafedirect Partners Limited (CPL) to hold all individual sets of shares together. In consultation with producer partners, the ownership of the PPP was transferred from Cafedirect plc to the producers themselves. It became clear that a charitable foundation would be best placed to fill this role and so CPF was formed in December 2009 and is wholly owned by CPL.    
CPF now wishes to ensure that it is genuinely producer-led; that male and female smallholder representatives are in a position to take leadership roles in governance and operations; and that all constituents are aware of and understand CPF and its activities. This will ensure that activities are relevant and responsive to the needs of producers, funds can be managed locally (rather than in the UK) and that producer partners will be able to connect directly with fundraising, networking and partnership development opportunities in their regions.</narrative>
  </description>
